The Ogun State Police Command is on the hunt for the Facebook user who posted money ritual on the platform where the Ogun teenage boys accused of murdering a girlfriend found it.
The four teenage suspects arrested by the police are Soliu Majekodunmi, 18; Wariz Oladehinde, 18; Abdulgafar Lukman, 19; and Balogun Mustaqeem, 20.
January 29, the four boys conspired, and murdered Sofiat, cut of her head, and ground the skull in a pot.
After their arrest, the suspect said they got the video instruction for the money ritual on Facebook.
According to Ogun police spokesman, Abimbola Oyeyemi,  the state police command would ensure all those directly or indirectly involved in the killing.
